\i0 \cf0 \'93Begging your pardon, sir,\'94 Annabel heard someone saying, but there were tears stinging her eyes. The man was holding her arms so tight she really thought he might break them. \'93The girl is my charge. I assure you, she meant no offence. She is silly, you understand. My apologies, the girl gave me the slip. I do hope she hasn\'92t been bothering you too severely?\'94
\i \

\i0 Finally, Annabel turned to look at the man. She recognized him immediately, even with her eyes a-blur with tears. The albino handed a few coins to the brute, who relinquished his grip on Annabel\'92s arms, took the coins. He seized his wife\'92s necklace from Annabel\'92s trembling hand and returned it to his wife.
\i \

\i0 \'93Just see to it that this doesn\'92t happen again,\'94 he said with a growl.
\i \

\i0 \'93Yes, sir,\'94 was the albino\'92s reply. There was the hint of an American accent to his voice, though Annabel couldn\'92t place the dialect. Just that he sounded a bit different from other upper class gentlemen.
\i \

\i0 Annabel looked up at her mysterious benefactor, wondering if she ought to flee. If he had rescued her only to enact his own form of retribution. But curiosity kept her.
\i \

\i0 \'93What do you want?\'94 she asked.
\i \

\i0 \'93Nothing at all,\'94 he answered.
\i \

\i0 \'93Then why help me?\'94 she spat.
\i \

\i0 \'93I didn\'92t like how he was treating you, and I felt I was in a position to help you,\'94 he answered.
\i \

\i0 Annabel studied his face to see if she was lying. If he was, he was a very clever liar. 
\i She still didn\'92t understand why he\'92d helped her though.\

\i0 After that, she began seeing him more and more. Occasionally, he would buy her presents; little
